{
  "title": "ISic000539. Fragment of Latin inscription on a marble arch",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucius · Seius · Luci · filius · Aemila tribu Fir\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucius\">L(ucius)</span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Seius\">Seius</span> · <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Luci\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Luci\">L(uci)</span></span> · f(ilius) · Aem(ila) (<em>scil.</em> tribu) <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Fir\"><span data-text=\"Fir\">Fir</span></span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>P · pec [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] inpen[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Lucius · Seius · Luci · filius · Aemila tribu Fir\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Lucius\">L</span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Seius\">SEIUS</span>·<span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Luci\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Luci\">L</span></span>·F·AEM(<em>scil.</em> TRIBU)<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Fir\"><span data-text=\"Fir\">FIR</span></span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>P·PEC[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]INPEN[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text of CIL, after Gualtherus and Cordici</span>  </span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Gualtherus: FIR omitted, lacuna marked; FIR recorded by Ventimiglia (so Mommsen); Cordici: I·PCC, later deleted</span></span><br></li><li><span class=\"2\">2: <span>Cordici: EFFE·INPEN, later deleted</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Manganaro and Mommsen both noted that the name L.Seius also appears on coins of Panhormus as proconsul of Sicily, in the late Augustan period, and identification with the L. Seius here, making a dedication at Erice, would be attractive, but far from certain. The consul of 18 CE seems less likely, as his cognomen Tubero does not seem to align with the traces variously recorded at the end of line 1 in the antiquarian tradition. P.PEC might be p(osuit) pec(unia). </p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 156 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a></li><li> Castelli 1769 cl. 7, no. 24 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084</a></li><li> Castelli 1784 cl. 7, no. 25 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083</a></li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\" target=\"_blank\">7259</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li><li> Manganaro 1987 583 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001833\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001833</a></li><li> Manganaro 1988 22 n.83 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a></li><li> Bivona 2000 155 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002135\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002135</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
  "divs": [
    {
